      p After dark, we had a few missions, first we wanted to scope out train tickets for our trip to Mt. Koya the next day. We also wanted to explore the lively Dotonburi area. 
      P We walked over to Namba Station to find out about the train to Mt. Koya. This train is not part of the JR network so it needs to be purchased separately. It makes sense to buy the inclusive Koyasan-World Heritage Ticket. This includes the train back and forth, the cable car up the mountain after you arrive, and the local buses in Mt. Koya. It also includes some tourist discounts that we didn't use. We bought the tickets for a specific time the next day. 
      p We walked to the main nightlife area, Dotonburi. Unfortunately, it ended up being another evening where we endlessly walked around looking for a restaurant where we could eat. After almost giving up, we checked out a bar that advertised having Italian food. It ended up being perfect pasta. It was a great find.
